This is a weekly update of the status of @themesopotamians system.

Spun up Hammurabi this week, and with the price drop I'm beginning to buy in with a plan to move forward on the higher levels. The autovoter is working well, the HF20 vote-delay code is testing perfectly on one of my other projects, there's a script automatically making crossover votes to other levels when VP is above 99, and the stats are taken from the blockchain automatically. So the only thing I still have to figure out is how to use them to make posts, and I'll be able to concentrate on the curation posts and the social aspect of things, as we're getting more activity in the Discord.

The roadmap has Ashurbanipal in December and Gilgamesh in February, but that seems pretty unlikely at this point. I'm thinking about doing both of them as soon as HF20 is stable. Level 6 won't have open applications, it will only be for people leveling into it through the program, so that one can be put off a little.

