This is a weekly update of the status of @themesopotamians system.

With our autovoter running a little slower than SteemAuto, probably due to the fact that it's sitting in my office rather than next to a node, I'm starting to see some pending curation rewards, even with votes coming in on the first minute on average. Picking up some extra SP that way would be a nice benefit that I hadn't really figured in the system math - it will be interesting to see what that looks like when we move to fifteen-minute voting in a few weeks, and integrate it into the plan. Still going to keep them coming as fast as possible until HF20. 

By next week's update Hammurabi should be running. 

