This is a weekly update of the status of @themesopotamians system.

I got a way-too-good-to-refuse offer to lease my delegation this week, so my own votes into the system are going to drop significantly for a month or so. In return I get a nice boost of liquidity that will solidify my financial ability to launch Hammurabi in September as planned.

Financial ability isn't the only concern, though. I'm not quite running at capacity operating the accounts and making these posts but it would sure be nice to make them easier before we expand too much. So my goal for the rest of July is to get the voting system automated, with the hope that I can have it running by the time I leave for Copenhagen on August 7. Then after I get back from August 18 on I'll be working on automating the statistics posts. Once those things are done, we should be able to get the whole system going in time to support our current users as they move up in levels. 

This week I'm going to be moving around the voting of the inactive accounts, because we got a surprise delegation from @davemccoy and it might be nice to be able to accept others. If you want to comment on that please see the previous post here.



